Also, we took him to ride the carousel till the train opened   . The sign on the carousel said it opened at 10, I was told that the hours differ in the winter and that it didn’t open till 12. There is no sign that says hours differ and when I said something about it to the person I spoke with in the security office said he thought about changing the sign but hasn’t. This is a very sad experience.

name: Cary Reams
text: The Dauphin Island Bridge - formerly known as the Gordon Persons Bridge, is approximately 3-miles long and connects mainland Alabama to Dauphin Island.  The bridge was originally constructed in 1955 but was destroyed in 1979 by Hurricane Fredrick and reopened in its current form in 1982.  It’s really a beautiful structure in need of more photographs here - and I’ll work on that next time I’m in this area!  Lastly, the bridge also marks the dividing line between the Mississippi Sound on the West and the Mobile Bay on the East!  Enjoy your crossing!
